{"kind":"notes","id":"nt/nshi4k","slide":1,"text":"Hi, I am Milton Estuardo Torres Meraz, a software developer in the Persuasive Computing Lab at Dalhousie University. My project, Iron Quest 3D, is a sensor-fusion engine for physical interaction. It combines camera-based pose and dumbbell detection with ESP32 and IMU telemetry, plus Garmin heart-rate context, and converts them into normalized signals such as arm extension, stability and exertion. The current goal is to prove the middleware before building the final game layer."}